This little perl-script lets you save mime attachments of an E-Mail to a specific folder automatically.
My first intention for this script was a little photoblog, where I could send pictures I took via mobile phone to a special E-Mail-Adress and having them appear in the blog instantly.

I used it in combination with procmail:

:0:
* ^From.*marlo@dermarlo.de
| ~/mime_attach.pl

